## Testing Approach

### Unit Tests
- Test individual functions in isolation
- Mock external dependencies
- Cover happy path and error cases
- Test boundary conditions

### Integration Tests
- Test component interactions
- Use realistic test data
- Verify end-to-end flows

### Test Organization
- Group related tests logically
- Use descriptive test names
- Follow project test conventions
- Add test documentation where needed

## Completion Criteria

Mark your subtask complete when:
- [ ] All specified test scenarios are covered
- [ ] Tests are well-organized and documented
- [ ] All tests pass locally
- [ ] No flaky or unreliable tests

## Output

When complete, provide:
1. Test files created/modified
2. Test coverage summary
3. Key test scenarios covered
4. Any known limitations or edge cases not tested
